-- India's Monsoon Is 13% Below Normal in June 1 to July 14 Period, IMD Says
-- Abhay Singh
-- 2010-07-14T13:50:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/india-s-monsoon-is-13-below-normal-in-june-1-to-july-14-period-imd-says.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, was 13 percent
below normal as of today, the weather office said.  
 The nation received 254.5 millimeters of rain in the June
1-July 14 period, compared with the 50-year average of 292.5
millimeters, the India Meteorological Department said on its
website. The monsoon was 16 percent below normal in June.  
 Rainfall was 16 percent below normal in northwest India,
including Uttar Pradesh state, and 14 percent below average in
central states including Madhya Pradesh, the agency said.  
          
          


  


        